    "body": "This PR is to fix an assertion regarding handling of PaddedSharedEncodingAttr. It is also discussed in https://github.com/triton-lang/triton/pull/10164. Since this assertion is a blocker of our CI/CD, and the fix is straightforward, I separate it from the PR10164 and make this PR in an attempt to resolve it ASAP.\r\n\r\nAssertion is triggered when `toLinearLayout()` is called with a type of `PaddedSharedEncodingAttr`. Since `toLinearLayout()` does not handle `PaddedSharedEncodingAttr` and hence trigger an assertion complaining \"unknown attribute\".\r\n\r\nTo be pedantic, padded-shared-layout cannot be convert to a linear-layout, because linear-layout does not depict its padding part, which is likely why `toLinearLayout()` do not want to handle this encoding.\r\n\r\nThe fix is simple, just to differentiate the padded layout and other layout at caller side.",
    "created_at": "2026-04-30T16:01:11Z",
    "updated_at": "2026-05-20T06:18:52Z",
    "closed_at": "2026-05-20T00:09:37Z",
